item.title: TikTok star Taylor Rousseau Grigg's cause of death revealed
item.description: Taylor Rousseau Grigg, a 25-year-old TikTok influencer with over 1.4 million followers, passed away due to a severe asthma attack and complications from Addison's disease. Her husband Cameron announced her sudden death, praising her bravery and strength. Taylor was an organ donor, and her story raises awareness of her health struggles and enduring spirit.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Who is judge Arun Subramanian? New Judge assigned to Sean 'Diddy' Combs sex-trafficking case
item.description: Sean "Diddy" Combs' federal criminal sex trafficking case has been reassigned to Judge Arun Subramanian, providing Combs another chance to apply for bail. The trial date is set for May 5 in Manhattan. Combs, pleading not guilty, faces charges including sex trafficking by force, transportation for prostitution, and racketeering conspiracy.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Before becoming a King, Prince George wants to be ...
item.description: Prince George, could break the royal tradition of serving in the Armed Forces before becoming King, aspires to be a chef. During a visit to Wiveton Hall Cafe, he expressed interest in working with a wood-fired pizza oven. Sadly, the cafe is closing next month due to rising costs and staffing issues.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: ‘I could feel my house shaking’: Milton tears across Florida
item.description: Hurricane Milton caused severe destruction in Florida, killing at least 10 people and knocking out power to over 3 million homes. Tampa's Tropicana Field was damaged, and St. Lucie County faced deadly tornadoes. Residents like Greg Cruz and Alex Franceschi shared harrowing experiences, while concerns grow over Fort Myers Beach's future amid rising property transformations.

item.title: Almost 10 million pounds of meat recalled in US after listeria risk
item.description: BrucePac recalls 9.9 million pounds of ready-to-eat meat and poultry products due to potential listeria contamination discovered during USDA testing. Though no illnesses are reported yet, symptoms can take up to 10 weeks to appear. The affected items were distributed nationwide, and the USDA advises disposal or return of these products.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Donald Trump's youngest daughter Tiffany is pregnant, former president says
item.description: Tiffany Trump, daughter of Donald Trump and Marla Maples, is expecting her first child with husband Michael Boulos. Raised in California, she graduated from Georgetown Law. Known for her low profile, Tiffany supported her father during his presidency and in legal matters. Michael, born in Lebanon, aids Trump’s reelection efforts, engaging with Arab and Muslim American leaders.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Colorado gold mine: 1 dead, 12 trapped after elevator malfunction
item.description: A fatal accident at Colorado's Mollie Kathleen Gold Mine left one person dead and 12 trapped after an elevator failure. Eleven others were rescued. Emergency crews are working to repair the elevator to reach the remaining trapped individuals. Rescuers maintain radio contact and are prepared for a rope rescue if necessary.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump’s Flagrant podcast appearance hits 1.5m views, outdoing Harris' media blitz
item.description: As the US presidential election approaches, Kamala Harris and Donald Trump intensify media engagements. Harris appears on popular shows like The Late Show and Call Her Daddy, while Trump features on the Flagrant podcast. Trump's interview garners more views quickly. Polls indicate a tight race, with Harris slightly leading Trump.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Get a life, man': Biden fires back at Trump over hurricane misinformation
item.description: President Biden rebukes former President Trump, urging him to prioritize aiding hurricane victims after allegations of a slow federal response. Biden highlights ongoing federal support and denounces misinformation. He praises Floridians for following evacuation orders and warns of remaining dangers post-Hurricane Milton.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Pakistan: Islamabad, Rawalpindi to shut businesses for five days ahead of SCO summit
item.description: Islamabad and Rawalpindi will shut down businesses and several public services from October 12 to 16 for security reasons ahead of the SCO summit. The event will see leaders like China's Premier Li Qiang and India's Foreign Minister S. Jaishankar, marking his first visit to Pakistan.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump proposes new tax breaks, promises to end double taxation for Americans abroad
item.description: Donald Trump announced tax break proposals, including making car loan interest tax-deductible and ending double taxation for Americans abroad, aimed at swaying voters in key states. Economists are skeptical about funding and benefits, pointing to a potential increase in national debt. Audience reactions were mixed, reflecting varying opinions on his financial strategies.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: New York man killed by a group of dogs in backyard
item.description: A 59-year-old man was killed by a group of dogs in Schenectady. Officers found James Provost being attacked by eight to nine mixed-breed pit bull dogs and one officer discharged his weapon to stop the attack. Authorities removed 24 dogs from the residence.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'She has no role...': What Florida governor DeSantis said about Harris's involvement in hurricane response
item.description: Florida governor Ron DeSantis criticised Kamala Harris for attempting to involve herself in the hurricane response, stating she has no role in it. DeSantis emphasised his collaboration with President Joe Biden and FEMA, accusing Harris of politicising the disaster for her campaign.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: TD Bank pleads guilty to money laundering violations, agrees to $3 billion penalty
item.description: TD Bank, the largest bank to date to admit to US Bank Secrecy Act violations, pleads guilty to money laundering-related charges and agrees to $3 billion in penalties. The Justice Department cites pervasive compliance failures over a decade. An asset cap limits TD's US operations, and CEO Bharat Masrani plans to retire, taking responsibility for the issues.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Has Kate Middleton given up on reuniting Prince William and Prince Harry? What royal experts say
item.description: Kate Middleton has ceased mediating between Prince William and Prince Harry. After completing preventive chemotherapy, she is now prioritizing her health and family. Tensions persist within the royal family, with minimal communication between Harry, Meghan, and the palace.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Ethel Kennedy, wife of Robert F Kennedy, dies at 96​​
item.description: Ethel Kennedy, widow of Robert F Kennedy, passed away at 96 due to complications from a stroke. A resilient matriarch, she maintained the Kennedy legacy while raising 11 children. Kennedy founded the Robert F Kennedy Centre for Justice and Human Rights, advocating for social causes throughout her life. She is remembered for her enduring strength and contributions to maintaining the Kennedy family's legacy.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: NYT-Siena poll indicates Democrats may soon lose Senate control
item.description: The upcoming senate elections could shift power to Republicans, with Montana's Jon Tester trailing Tim Sheehy 52% to 44%, impacting Democrats' slim majority. Significant advertising spending underscores the contentious race, while other key Democratic-held Senate seats also face tight competition.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Still a principled conservative': Meghan McCain reveals why she is not endorsing Trump or Harris
item.description: Meghan McCain confirms she will not endorse either Kamala Harris or Donald Trump in the upcoming election, citing her commitment to being a principled conservative like her late father, John McCain. Despite her brother Jimmy's endorsement of Harris, Meghan maintains there is no family drama.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Kate Middleton, Prince William reunite for first joint appearance after her chemotherapy
item.description: Prince William and Kate visited Southport to meet families of the three girls murdered at a Taylor Swift-themed event in July. This marked Kate's first public engagement since ending her chemotherapy treatment. The couple aimed to show support to the community recovering from the attack, which had sparked nationwide riots and disinformation.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Oops' moment for BBC: Apology issued after weather app gaffe shows 'hurricane winds' in London
item.description: The BBC apologizes for a technical error in its weather app that incorrectly forecasted extreme weather conditions, including hurricane-force winds and temperatures of 404°C. The Met Office provides accurate updates, noting the UK's expected weather and ruling out the current possibility of hurricane impacts.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk
